# Network Traffic Analysis Report

## Executive Summary

Network traffic was captured and analyzed using Wireshark in a virtual lab environment.

The investigation focused on understanding communication between hosts and identifying suspicious network activity.

---

## Scope

- DNS Analysis
- HTTP Analysis
- TCP Analysis
- ICMP Analysis

---

## Activities Performed

- Live Packet Capture
- Protocol Inspection
- Traffic Filtering
- Packet Analysis
- Communication Tracking

---

## Findings

- DNS requests successfully analyzed.
- HTTP communication inspected.
- TCP handshake observed.
- ICMP packets monitored.
- Packet headers reviewed.

---

## Recommendations

- Monitor abnormal traffic.
- Use encrypted protocols where possible.
- Review unusual DNS requests.
- Investigate unexpected outbound connections.

---

## Conclusion

The project demonstrates practical experience in packet capture, protocol analysis, and network traffic investigation using Wireshark.
